  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Danwadaag Durable Solutions (DS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Danwadaag project aims to create an environment for durable solutions through a multi-stakeholder and sectoral, rights and needs based programming. The project focuses on: (1) Strengthening Government leadership and capacity to enable Durable Solutions processes at Federal Member States (FMS)/Banadir Regional Authority (BRA) and district level; (2) Enabling targeted displacement affected communities to increase decision making and increase access to basics services using physical, material and legal safety priorities; (3) Increasing self-reliance of displacement affected communities through inclusive, sustainable economic opportunities in partnership with the local private sector, development and resilience actors; and (4) Ensuring that durable solutions programming and decision making processes at national and regional level are informed by knowledge and evidence generated by the programme. The project is premised on the theory of change that : If government capacity is strengthened to lead (re)integration and create conducive environments for durable solution processes based on safety, voluntariness and dignity; build a collaborative culture of adaptive learning &amp; management; ensure specific displacement related needs &amp; vulnerabilities are addressed for targeted displacement affected communities (host, returnees and IDPs); and catalyse economic opportunities; THEN (re)integration will be achieved for the targeted communities; thus, laying the foundation for access to sustainable durable solution processes for wider Displacement affected communities in South West State, Jubaland and Banadir.
 The project aims to deliver four outcomes:
 i. Strengthened Government leadership and capacity to enable Durable Solutions processes at Regional, FMS and district level
 ii. DACs have increased decision making, access and use of basic services using legal /material / physical safety criteria
 iii. DACs have increased self-reliance through inclusive sustainable economic opportunities co-created with local private sector, development partners, diaspora and government
 iv. Durable solutions programming and decision-making processes at national and regional level are informed by knowledge and evidence generated by the programme</narrative>
  </description>
